"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-02-parisolympics-fraser-pryce-clayton-forbes-100m-semis\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's trio of Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce, Tia Clayton and Shashalee Forbes all advanced automatically to the semi-finals of the women's 100m as the track and field competition at the Olympics got underway at Paris' Stade de France on Friday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9998851416425416, \"rank\": 6.631340191026569e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\"}, {\"begin\": 43, \"end\": 54, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tia_Clayton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tia Clayton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tia_Clayton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tia_Clayton\"}, {\"begin\": 59, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shashalee_Forbes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shashalee Forbes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shashalee_Forbes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shashalee_Forbes\"}, {\"begin\": 209, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999371668784, \"rank\": 6.283307214809617e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce, who is competing at her fifth and final Olympic Games, looked easy as she clocked 10.92 seconds (0.8m/s), her 86th sub-11 seconds race of her illustrious career, as she finished second behind Marie-Josee TaLou-Smith of the Ivory Coast who won in 10.87 seconds - fastest in theround with the Jamaican next best.\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 481, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9399633444138529, \"rank\": 0.05982099394376209, \"text\": \"Ivory Coast\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999965429449915, \"rank\": 3.4563707861282172e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clayton, running with a strapped-up right ham string, got off to a fast start before easing through the finish line in second place, running 11.00 seconds (1.2m/s) as Audrey Leduc ran a Canadian national record 10.95 seconds to win.\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Horne\", \"score\": 0.997877152871813, \"rank\": 0.0010685203947605804, \"text\": \"Audrey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Horne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Horne\"}, {\"begin\": 744, \"end\": 749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_the_petroleum_industry_in_Canada\", \"score\": 0.5494830459250792, \"rank\": 0.6289437292837441, \"text\": \"Leduc\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_the_petroleum_industry_in_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_the_petroleum_industry_in_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forbes, who was a last minute replacement for three-time national champion Shericka Jackson, was also second in her heat in 11.19 seconds (-0.4m/s) behind American Twanisha Terry's 11.15 seconds.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 879, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shericka Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 959, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.997815046351098, \"rank\": 0.0010893585420131537, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The semi-finals are set for 12:50pm Jamaican time on Saturday and the final set for 2:20pm.-Paul A Reid  Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1037, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999965429449915, \"rank\": 3.4563707861282172e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}]}"